JSVsaItemType Enum

Definition

Represents the type of the item.

In this Article

[System.Obsolete("Use of this type is not recommended because it is being deprecated in Visual Studio 2005; there will be no replacement for this feature. Please see the ICodeCompiler documentation for additional help.")]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComVisible(true)]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Guid("97453226-34DD-4379-B658-005DF8F84EA1")]
public enum JSVsaItemType
Inheritance
Object
ValueType
Enum
JSVsaItemType

Fields

AppGlobal

Used to add a global object to the .NET script engine. This type is used to create an IJSVsaGlobalItem object.
Code

Used to create a code item for storing source code for the .NET script engine.
Reference

Used to add a reference to an external .NET assembly, which can then be referenced from code. This type is used to create an IJSVsaReferenceItem object
